public class PaymentFormActivity
extends android.app.Activity

Standalone Payment "form" activity. The Activity includes an VTComboCardView, allowing the user to select a Venmo Touch card or enter a new card. Upon success, the user's choice will be returned in the activity's result data Intent.

Starting the Activity

You must start this activity using Activity.startActivityForResult(Intent, int) with an Intent generated by either getStartIntent(Context, String, String) or getSandboxStartIntent(Context, String, String).

Interpreting Results

Process results from this Activity by by passing the result "data" intent (as received in your activity's Activity.onActivityResult(int, int, android.content.Intent)) to processResultIntent(Intent, ActivityResultHandler).

There are three possible results from this Activity, each corresponding to a method on the PaymentFormActivity.ActivityResultHandler that you pass in. Exactly one of these methods will be called:

  • Cancelled: The activity ended without a payment method being selected (PaymentFormActivity.ActivityResultHandler.onCancelled()).
  • Venmo Touch card selected: The user selected a previously-saved card (PaymentFormActivity.ActivityResultHandler.onCardSelected(CardStub)).
  • New card entered: The user added a new card (PaymentFormActivity.ActivityResultHandler.onCardAdded(CardDetails, boolean, Map)).
